
[1]perquisite

   PER'QUISITE, n. s as z. [L.perquisitus, perquiro; per and quoero, to
   seek.] A fee or pecuniary allowance to an officer for services, beyond
   his ordinary salary or settled wages; or a fee allowed by law to an
   officer for a specific service, in lieu of an annual salary. [The
   latter is the common acceptation of the word in American.]
